The paper deals with the detection and removal of hidden information in images using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a quantitative metric and comparison with conventional steganalysis methods suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of adaptive pixel-level removal suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
